Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["", "SlideShowNavigationBar",
 CellTags->
  "SlideShowHeader",ExpressionUUID->"d5b898a3-c58b-4e97-98fb-c09bb44cf0d6"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Extracting Data", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"7663a64c-5c0e-478d-af6a-1f3823266222"],

Cell["\<\
Extracting data from websites involves fetching a webpage\[CloseCurlyQuote]s \
content and parsing it to retrieve specific information, such as text, images \
or links. The process takes advantage of the fact that webpages typically \
have a consistent format. This consistency can be exploited to build \
automated tools that navigate a website\[CloseCurlyQuote]s structure and \
extract the desired information.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d3e3c2bd-b4af-4361-8853-0a17de32bd49"],

Cell["\<\
The main advantage of automated extraction is that it allows the collection \
of large amounts of data that would be impractical to collect manually. This \
information can be used on its own, or it can be combined with other \
programming methods, workflows and technologies.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"2aa74930-f630-47a1-bd97-a2fe5504528a"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["", "EndOfSlide",ExpressionUUID->"46c72855-53ed-4a7e-be75-c1ad1c5e1a8b"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["", "SlideShowNavigationBar",
 CellTags->
  "SlideShowHeader",ExpressionUUID->"1108cd7b-6fab-46dd-8d2d-f1b4f6b6920f"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Why Extract Data?", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"06d40a41-ccb2-4b50-b879-6b7b949907e0"],

Cell["\<\
Typically, you would want to extract data from the web to do some further \
computation on it. While the functionality of Wolfram Language is extensive \
and easy to use, the main advantage it provides is that any data that you get \
is immediately available for computation with the rest of the functionality \
found in Wolfram Language. Once you get your data, it is in an environment \
where you can start doing image processing, machine learning, visualisation, \
LLM training and much more.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"053a763f-680e-45dc-9faa-8b0105a55e2b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Throughout this webinar, we will be using the data we obtain with various \
visualisation techniques, dynamic elements, statistical analyses and AI \
integration, but the general point to keep in mind is that once your data is \
in Wolfram Language, it is immediately subject to the 6000+ built-in \
functions and 3000+ ",
 ButtonBox["community-contributed functions",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://resources.wolframcloud.com/FunctionRepository/all"], None},
  ButtonNote->"https://resources.wolframcloud.com/FunctionRepository/all"],
 ":"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"fe519cb5-dddd-4075-bf88-add345ac61f6"],

